ballers]]\n[[Category:Bulgaria under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:First Professional Football League (Bulgaria) players]]\n[[Category:PFC Litex Lovech players]]\n[[Category:PFC CSKA Sofia players]]\n[[Category:Cagliari Calcio players]]\n[[Category:SK Sturm Graz players]]\n[[Category:People from Kresna]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Austrian Football Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Austria]]\n", "text_old": "{{Eastern Slavic name|Vasilev|Despodov}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Kiril Despodov\n| image          = Despodov 2018.jpg\n| caption        = Despodov warming up for [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]] in October 2018\n| fullname       = Kiril Vasilev Despodov\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1996|11|11|df=yes}}\n| birth_place    = [[Kresna]], [[Bulgaria]]\n| height         = 1.79 m\n| position       = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]], [[Forward (association football)|forward]]\n| currentclub    = [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]] (on loan from [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]])\n| clubnumber     = 11\n| youthyears1    = 2007\u20132008 \n| youthclubs1    = Pirin 2001<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.24chasa.bg/Article.asp?ArticleId=1616623 |title=Kiril Despodov interview |publisher=24chasa.bg |accessdate=2 November 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121103225133/http://www.24chasa.bg/Article.asp?ArticleId=1616623 |archivedate= 3 November 2012 }}</ref>\n| youthyears2    = 2008\u20132015 \n| youthclubs2    = [[Litex Lovech]]\n| years1         = 2012\u20132016 \n| clubs1         = [[Litex Lovech]]       \n| caps1          = 37 \n| goals1         = 4\n| years2         = 2016\u20132019     \n| clubs2         = [[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]]         \n| caps2          = 71\n| goals2         = 20\n| years3         = 2019\u2013\n| clubs3         = [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]]         \n| caps3          = 4\n| goals3         = 0\n| years4         = 2019\u2013\n| clubs4         = \u2192 [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]] (loan)   \n| caps4          = 10\n| goals4         = 6\n| nationalyears1 = 2012\u20132013 \n| nationalteam1  = [[Bulgaria national under-17 football team|Bulgaria U17]] \n| nationalcaps1  = 9 \n| nationalgoals1 = 5 \n| nationalyears2 = 2012\u20132015 \n| nationalteam2  = [[Bulgaria national under-19 football team|Bulgaria U19]] \n| nationalcaps2  = 17 \n| nationalgoals2 = 5\n| nationalyears3 = 2015\u20132018 \n| nationalteam3  = [[Bulgaria national under-21 football team|Bulgaria U21]] \n| nationalcaps3  = 20 \n| nationalgoals3 = 6\n| nationalcaps4  = 1\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| nationalyears5 = 2017\u2013\n| nationalteam5  = [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]]\n| nationalcaps5  = 12\n| nationalgoals5 = 1\n| club-update    = 30 November 2019 (UTC)\n| ntupdate       = {{date|2019-11-17}}\n}}\n'''Kiril Despodov''' ({{lang-bg|\u041a\u0438\u0440\u0438\u043b \u0414\u0435\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0432}}; born 11 November 1996) is a [[Bulgaria]]n professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]] side [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]], on loan from [[Serie A]] club [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]], and the [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgarian national team]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.worldfootball.net/spieler_profil/kiril-despodov/ | title = Kiril Despodov | publisher = worldfootball.net | accessdate = 1 September 2012}}</ref> He primarily plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] but can also play as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].\n\nDespodov made his way through the youth teams at [[PFC Litex Lovech|Litex Lovech]] before making his senior debut in 2012 at the age of 15. He was transferred to [[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]] in June 2016, where he established himself as the team's star player, winning the [[Bulgarian Footballer of the Year]] award in 2018 - the first CSKA player to do so since [[Hristo Stoichkov]] in 1989.\n\nOn 23 March 2018, Despodov made his senior international debut for Bulgaria in a 1\u20130 friendly loss against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]].\n\n==Career==\n===Litex Lovech===\nDespodov was born in [[Kresna]]. He joined [[PFC Litex Lovech|Litex Lovech]]'s Academy at the age of 12 and progressed through the club's youth system. He played an important role in Litex's 2012 [[Bulgarian Football Union|BFU]] U-16 Cup win, scoring two goals in the final against [[PFC Cherno More Varna|Cherno More]] on 26 April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.e-79.com/news-52667.html|publisher=e-79.com|title=\u0422\u0430\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0442 \u043e\u0442 \u041a\u0440\u0435\u0441\u043d\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0441\u0438 \u043a\u0443\u043f\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u041b\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0441|date=26 April 2012|language=Bulgarian}}</ref>\n\nDespodov made his first team debut under [[Hristo Stoichkov]]'s management,<ref>{{cite web|author=Anastasov, Anatoli|publisher=7sport.net|title=\u0418\u0446\u043e \u0431\u0438\u043b \u043b\u043e\u0448, \u0430?|url=http://www.7sport.net/archive7ds/2012/10/09/fb_1footbg/d6597_9.htm|date=9 October 2012|accessdate=25 July 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725223114/http://www.7sport.net/archive7ds/2012/10/09/fb_1footbg/d6597_9.htm|archive-date=25 July 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> at 15 years 183 days, in a 5\u20130 [[Bulgarian A Football Group|league]] win over [[PFC Kaliakra Kavarna|Kaliakra Kavarna]] on 12 May 2012, coming on as a substitute for [[Svetoslav Todorov]].<ref>{{cite web|author=|publisher=lovechtoday.eu|title=\u041b\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0441 \u0433\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0438 5:0 \u041a\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0430\u043a\u0440\u0430 |url=http://lovechtoday.eu/%D0%BB%D0%B8%D1%82%D0%B5%D0%BA%D1%81-%D0%B3%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BC%D0%B8-50-%D0%BA%D0%B0%D0%BB%D0%B8%D0%B0%D0%BA%D1%80%D0%B0/|date=13 May 2012|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 10 August 2013, netting the fifth in a 5\u20131 away league win over [[PFC Pirin Gotse Delchev|Pirin Gotse Delchev]].\n\nOn 22 November 2014, Despodov scored his first goal of the 2014\u201315 season against [[PFC Cherno More Varna|Cherno More]] in a 3\u20130 away win. On 27 November, he signed his first professional contract with Litex shortly after turning 18.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.blitz.bg/sport/article/253586|publisher=blitz.bg|title=\u041b\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0441 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0430 \u0441 \u0442\u0430\u043b\u0430\u043d\u0442|date=27 November 2014|language=Bulgarian}}</ref> Two days later he scored his second goal of the season in a 2\u20132 away draw against [[PFC Levski Sofia|Levski Sofia]] in the 66th minute to clinch a point for his team.\n\nDespite the not so good start of the season 2015\u201316 for Despodov, as he played only in 4 matches from 19 rounds, he became a hero in the quarterfinals of the Bulgarian Cup. In the match against [[Levski Sofia]], after coming on as a subtitude in the 76th minute when the match was 0\u20130 and Litex was down to 10 people, they eventually ended up winning the game after extra time 3\u20130, with Despodov scoring 2 of the goals.<ref>[http://www.sportal.bg/news.php?news=579765 10 \u043e\u0442 \u041b\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0441 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043f\u0438\u043b\u044f\u0445\u0430 \u041b\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0432 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0442\u0430 ]</ref><ref>[http://www.sportal.bg/news.php?news=579907 \u0413\u0435\u0440\u043e\u044f\u0442 \u0437\u0430 \u041b\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043a\u0441: \u0412\u0441\u0438\u0447\u043a\u0438 \u0441\u043c\u0435 \u043c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0449\u0430\u0441\u0442\u043b\u0438\u0432\u0438]</ref>\n\n===CSKA Sofia===\n{{expand section|date=January 2019}}\nOn 29 April 2017, Despodov scored his first goal in [[The Eternal Derby]], netting the second in CSKA Sofia's 3\u20130 win over [[Levski Sofia]] in a [[First Professional Football League]] match.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://topsport.bg/a-group/na-zhivo-levski-tsska-0-3-sinite-sa-v-nokdaun.html|publisher=topsport.bg|title=\u041d\u0410 \u0416\u0418\u0412\u041e: \u041b\u0435\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0438 - \u0426\u0421\u041a\u0410 0:3, \"\u0441\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435\" \u0441\u0430 \u0432 \u043d\u043e\u043a\u0434\u0430\u0443\u043d!|date=29 April 2017|accessdate=7 May 2017|language=Bulgarian}}</ref>\n\n===Cagliari===\nOn 30 January 2019, Despodov completed a transfer to [[Serie A]] side [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]], signing a contract until 2023 with an extension option for one more season. CSKA Sofia did not reveal the exact transfer fee, but it was reported that it broke the record for an outgoing [[First Professional Football League (Bulgaria)|First League]] transfer of a local Bulgarian player, which until then was [[Hristo Stoichkov]]'s [[United States dollar|$]] 4.5 million move to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in the summer of 1990.<ref name=\"CagliariSportal\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sportal.bg/news.php?news=768445 |title=\u041e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u043d\u043e: \u041a\u0430\u043b\u044f\u0440\u0438 \u0438 \u0426\u0421\u041a\u0410-\u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0432\u0438\u0445\u0430 \u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0441\u0444\u0435\u0440\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u041a\u0438\u0440\u0438\u043b \u0414\u0435\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0432 |date=30 January 2019 |publisher=sportal.bg |language=Bulgarian}}</ref> He made his debut for the club in a 3\u20130 away loss to [[A.C. Milan|Milan]] on 10 February, coming on for [[Artur Ioni\u021b\u0103]] in the 75th minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sportal.bg/news.php?news=770354 |title=\u041c\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043d \u0441\u0435 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438 \u0441 \u041a\u0430\u043b\u044f\u0440\u0438 \u0432 \u0434\u0435\u0431\u044e\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u041a\u0438\u0440\u0438\u043b \u0414\u0435\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0432 |date=10 February 2019 |publisher=sportal.bg |language=Bulgarian}}</ref>\n\n====Sturm Graz (loan)====\nOn 2 September 2019, Despodov was loaned to [[SK Sturm Graz|Sturm Graz]] for the 2019\u201320 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gong.bg/football-sviat/transferi/oficialno-el-maestro-i-despodov-se-sybraha-556542|title=\u041e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u043d\u043e: \u0429\u0443\u0440\u043c \u0413\u0440\u0430\u0446 \u043d\u0430\u0435 \u041a\u0438\u0440\u0438\u043b \u0414\u0435\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0432|date=2 September 2019|publisher=gong.bg|language=bulgarian}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nOn 7 February 2015, Despodov made his first appearance for [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]], in a goalless draw with [[Romania national football team|Romania]] in a non-official [[friendly match]], coming on as a late [[substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Stanislav Manolev]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=flashscore.com|title=Romania vs. Bulgaria 0:0|url=http://www.flashscore.com/match/6eMiivhM/#lineups;1|date=7 February 2015|accessdate=7 February 2015}}</ref> He was also called up in March 2017, for a 2018 World Cup qualifier against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]], but remained on the bench.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.flashscore.com/match/zBtaVVUE/#lineups;1|publisher=flashscore.com|title=Bulgaria NT vs. Netherlands NT 2:0|date=25 March 2017|accessdate=7 April 2017}}</ref> Despodov finally made his complete debut for Bulgaria on 23 March 2018 in a friendly match against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]], replacing [[Spas Delev]] shortly after the one hour mark.<ref>[https://www.sportal.bg/news.php?news=715898 \u0410\u0432\u0442\u043e\u0433\u043e\u043b \u043f\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f, \u043a\u0430\u043f\u0438\u0442\u0430\u043d\u044a\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u0411\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0435 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0432\u0435\u043d \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u043e\u043d]</ref>\n\nOn 13 October 2018, he scored his first goal for the national team in a 2\u20131 home win against [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]], in a match for the [[2018\u201319 UEFA Nations League]].\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===Club===\n{{updated|match played 30 November 2019}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club||rowspan=\"2\"|Season||colspan=\"2\"|League!!colspan=\"2\"|Cup!!colspan=\"2\"|Continental!!colspan=\"2\"|Other!!colspan=\"3\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[PFC Litex Lovech|Litex Lovech]]\n|[[2011\u201312 A Group|2011\u201312]]\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Bulgarian A Football Group|A Group]]\n|1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||1||0\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 A Group|2012\u201313]]\n|8||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||9||0\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 A Group|2013\u201314]]\n|6||2||4||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||10||2\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 A Group|2014\u201315]]\n|18||2||3||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||21||2\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 A Group|2015\u201316]]\n|4||0||5||2||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||7||2\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!37!!4!!13!!2!!0!!0!!0!!0!!50!!6\n|-\n|[[PFC Litex Lovech II|Litex Lovech II]]\n|[[2015\u201316 B Group|2015\u201316]]\n|[[Bulgarian B Football Group|B Group]]\n|13||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||13||2\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"|[[PFC CSKA Sofia II|CSKA Sofia II]]\n|[[2016\u201317 Second Professional Football League (Bulgaria)|2016\u201317]]\n|[[Second Professional Football League (Bulgaria)|Second League]]\n|1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||1||0\n|-\n|rowspan